Welcome to the ofskills exam lab.

This is an unprivileged Sysbox-style container running systemd as PID 1.

Deviations from a baremetal install:
  * Time sync (chrony/systemd-timesyncd) is masked; the host clock is authoritative.
  * Auditd, systemd-udevd, NetworkManager and systemd-modules-load are masked.
  * Block devices, kernel modules and most host-global sysctls are unavailable.
  * No firewall (firewalld/ufw/nftables) is installed.
  * Root account is locked; use `sudo -i` for a root shell.
  * `sudo` is configured NOPASSWD for the `user` account.

Run `systemctl list-unit-files --state=masked` to inspect masked units.

